		<div id="comment_body_65288307"><p>I fixed the subject for you.  USB4 version 2.0 (yes, I agree it's a dumb numbering scheme) has an 80 Gbps symmetric mode and 120/40 Gbps asymmetric mode.  So they've announced a sometimes-proprietary cable that has a standard connector, but the standard connector runs slower than what the rest of the world decided on 2+ years ago.  Being late to the party with a slow cable is not a flex.</p></div>
